title: Geth node does not fall into the correct chain of the ropsten test network
body:
Hello.
I have geth node version 1.10.18 running. After merging the networks and adding the parameter `--override.terminaltotaldifficulty=50000000000000000`. The logs keep repeating messages:
  | WARN [06-13|08:09:09.047] Local chain is post-merge, waiting for beacon client sync switch-over... 
  | INFO [06-13|08:09:09.153] Legacy sync reached merge threshold      number=12,357,771 hash=da871a..b1cd17 td=50,555,542,962,209,070 ttd=50,000,000,000,000,000
  | INFO [06-13|08:09:09.290] Legacy sync reached merge threshold      number=12,357,771 hash=da871a..b1cd17 td=50,555,542,962,209,070 ttd=50,000,000,000,000,000
  | INFO [06-13|08:09:09.476] Legacy sync reached merge threshold      number=12,357,771 hash=da871a..b1cd17 td=50,555,542,962,209,070 ttd=50,000,000,000,000,000


I read [here](https://geth.ethereum.org/docs/interface/merge) that now it is necessary to launch a beacon node, which, as a client, connects to the geth node. Launched it and synchronized. Beacon node logs, I don't see errors:

**My geth node is running in docker like this:**
version: '3.9'
services:
  ETH-test-node:
    image: ethereum/client-go:v1.10.18
    hostname: eth-test-node
    volumes:
      - "/mnt/data0/ethereum-test-data/root2/:/root"
    command:
      - --ropsten
      - --cache=1024
      - --nousb
      - --port=30303
      - --http 
      - --http.api=admin,debug,miner,txpool,personal,eth,net,web3
      - --http.port=8550
      - --http.addr=0.0.0.0 
      - --http.vhosts=*
      - --http.corsdomain=*
      - --metrics
      - --metrics.addr=0.0.0.0
      - --metrics.port=6060
      - --graphql 
      - --graphql.vhosts=* 
      - --ws
      - --ws.addr=0.0.0.0
      - --ws.port=8546
      - --ws.api=admin,debug,miner,txpool,personal,eth,net,web3
      - --ws.origins=*
      - --rpc.allow-unprotected-txs
      - --cache=1024 
      - --override.terminaltotaldifficulty=50000000000000000
    ports:
      - 30303:30303
      - 30303:30303/udp
      - 8550:8550
      - 8546:8546
      - 6060:6060

**My beacon node is running in docker like this:**
version: '3.7'
services:
  beacon-test-node:
    image: gcr.io/prysmaticlabs/prysm/beacon-chain:v2.1.3-rc.3
    hostname: beacon-test-node
    volumes:
      - "/mnt/data0/beacon-test-node/data:/data"
      - "/mnt/data0/beacon-test-node/genesis/genesis.ssz:/genesis/genesis.ssz"
    command:
      - --datadir=/data
      - --rpc-host=0.0.0.0
      - --monitoring-host=0.0.0.0
      - --http-web3provider=http://eth-test-node:8550
      - --genesis-state=/genesis/genesis.ssz
      - --terminal-total-difficulty-override=50000000000000000
      - --prater
      - --ropsten
      - --accept-terms-of-use
    ports:
      - 4000:4000
      - 13000:13000 
      - 12000:12000/udp


Please help me figure out what I did wrong?

I see this error in your logs: `Could not connect to execution client endpoint: could not make initial request to verify execution chain ID: wanted chain ID 5, got 3`. I think it's because you're passing `--prater` flag. Also I'm not sure if Prysm picks up the JWT secret that geth generates by default? you might need to pass that in.

@s1na  Thanks, I think I figured out my mistake.
But when I restart the node beacon sync with only flag `--ropsten`, it fails to complete it.
```
version: '3.9'
services:
  beacon-test-node:
    image: gcr.io/prysmaticlabs/prysm/beacon-chain:v2.1.3-rc.3
    hostname: beacon-test-node
    volumes:
      - "/mnt/data0/beacon-test-node/data1:/data"
      - "/mnt/data0/beacon-test-node/genesis1/genesis.ssz:/genesis/genesis.ssz"
    command:
      - --datadir=/data

      - --accept-terms-of-use
    ports:
      - 4000:4000

```
